lambda.name: persistVehicles
filterVehiclesInMemory
lambda.code:
const { sim, type, hub, x, y, vehicles } = input;

return vehicles.filter( v => 
  ( sim == null || v.sim.id === sim )
  && ( type == null || v.type.id === type )
  && ( hub == null || v.hub === hub )
  && ( x == null || v.x == x )
  && ( y == null || v.y == y )
)

lambda.code:
const { vehicle } = input

vehicle.cargo = vehicle.cargo.map( x => x.id )
vehicle.type = vehicle.type.id
vehicle.fuel = `${vehicle.id}/fuel`
vehicle.transitOrder = (vehicle.transitOrder) ? vehicle.transitOrder.id :  "Idle"

return vehicle
